    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="1368"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1368">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 412.11/64.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 9, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Minister for Foreign Affairs says the delay in taking up the claims has been
                    unavoidable owing to the extraordinary amount of work thrown on the consuls by
                    the disorders. His plan involves the transfer of the consul at Laredo to Douglas
                    and a consequent general shift of consular officers due to the incompetence of
                    several. A reply from the Governor of Coahuila is expected to-morrow, after
                    receipt of which arrangements will be completed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
